reviews:
Good place if you're looking a Taste the history of  Italian pizza,..(The favorite pizza dough, distinguished by its softness, flexibility and the  smoothness...Neapolitan Italian Taste...)+In addition to the quality & variety of orders :According to customers' request...In addition, it is a place that accommodates everyone, quiet even with family...
🤔===>The special thing is the Staff, they are very understanding of the customer, polite...& I would like to mention in particular Mr.#Fuad*****;a Professional Chef🫡 .

Now let me be clear that I was, as my friend told me, "3 sheets to the wind" after closing down The Middle East's "Xmortis" club night. I even forgot my tab was open.

With that disclaimer in mind, in that state this pizza was INCREDIBLE. Crust flavorful, toppings not loaded but so well distributed that it tasted excellent anyways. It wasn't especially large for $16 and change, but beggars can't be choosers at 2am. Walked back to my car with the pizza cradled to me with one arm, lid open, and I ate every single slice before I got there (where I slept, no way was I driving).

Atmosphere is an old in and out shop with burnt orange booths. It totally suits what it is, but I can't lie and say it's actually a lovely place, and just barely charismatic.

Will go back should ever I need!

Ordered a hamburger, mushroom, garlic pizza. Didn’t seem like there were enough toppings for the $3 per topping price.
One of the workers yelled at us for having the clumpy Parmesan cheese and red pepper flakes we had on the table. Understandable for people who orders to go, but not the way to go about it.
Quite hot in the restaurant. AC was on, but no cold air blowing. Felt cooler outside in the 85° weather.

Suggest to get the AC going so the cooks don’t drip their sweat on my pizza.

I've ordered delivery a few times from Cambridge Pizza, and while some have been good food delivered in a reasonable time, it's been very hit and miss. Today was a miss bad enough I think I'm going to stop ordering, despite my limited other options open that late.

The wait time, while long, wasn't really an issue for me. What was an issue was that my food arrived in very poor condition. The wrap, which is made with sauce and wet ingredients, had been sliced in half through the foil wrapper, then wrapped up, so the entire tortilla was soggy and covered in oil and some filling, and there were pieces of foil inside the two halves of the wrap that I had to pick out. My Cheesy Garlic bread, meanwhile, had not spent enough time in the oven; the cheese had only partially melted, and the bread was still very underbaked - soft, squishy, and doughy.

Another problem for me is that there is no way to contact them via text. Contact Us just lists their address, and while they have a phone number, that's just for ordering, and I see no point in calling to complain to the person who didn't care enough to make the food properly in the first place.

Chicken pesto pizza! Great cheese and not greasy at all. The wings Buffalo and crispy but not too burnt, also had good meat on them. Meatball sub was a surprise a lot better than I expected with lettuce on it. 5/5 delicious!
